ScheduleItem.Synopsis: When a baby is stolen from her mother in a grocery store, Detectives Benson and Stabler soon discover that the kidnapping is only the tip of the iceberg in a baby snatching and selling scheme. The detectives are led to private adoption lawyer Mark Sanford who, over ten years ago, had brokered the adoption of a child kidnapped from his mother who was murdered. Captain Cragen renews his pursuit of the case, opening old wounds with the parents of the murdered woman and creating new wounds with the adoptive family and biological father of the long-ago stolen child.

When a series of increasingly violent rapes occurs in an African-American community, Detectives Benson and Stabler are quick to suspect a known sex-offender recently released from prison. But as their leads grow cold, the case becomes personal for Detective Tutuola when the daughter of friends he grew up with becomes a fatal victim, and her distraught brother Rodney Thompson accuses the squad of putting insufficient resources into tracking the killer. As the detectives search for clues, a fifth victim is murdered and her final moments--along with Thompson's persistence--may provide the evidence needed to solve the case.

Detective Stabler finds himself paired with a brusque and opinionated cop, John "Hawk" Hawkins, who has become embittered with his job and personal life. The two work to capture a serial rapist/murderer whom Hawk originally nabbed years ago, but the more they learn about the new crimes he's suspected of, the more apparent it becomes that the recently released convict is not the culprit -- leading Hawk to realize that he may have convicted the wrong man.

The sexual assault of a heroin addict leads Detectives Benson and Stabler to the gruesome discovery of a decomposing baby's finger in the victim's purse. As they search for both the rapist and the identity of the baby, the detectives find that their assault victim might be withholding information to protect her icy mother or her protective grandmother. The case resonates with former narcotics detective Tutuola, who tries to help the young woman get clean.

When Rebecca Tolliver reports that her daughter Katie, a 22-year-old woman with Down Syndrome, has been raped and is now pregnant, Detectives Benson and Stabler face the delicate task of determining if Katie was indeed sexually assaulted--or if her over-protective mother is in denial that her daughter has chosen to consummate her relationship with her boyfriend. In the course of the investigation, the detectives make the disturbing discovery that more than one man had the opportunity to abuse Katie and that her naivety about sex may have put her at a heightened risk for such an attack. The case is further complicated when Katie and her mother disagree about her ability to keep her child, forcing Cabot to take sides and take on her superior.

The discovery of a man and woman stabbed during a seemingly romantic park rendezvous leaves Detectives Benson and Stabler with the gruesome job of identifying the victims -- a difficult task as the woman's head and hands are missing. However, when further analysis of the park reveals that the crime scene was staged, the detectives focus their investigation on the female victim and her career as a Manhattan Federation for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals officer, which leads them to a variety of associates on both sides of the animal rights issue.

When a fourteen-year-old girl is saved from jumping in front of a train, SVU is called in to help her. She falsely accuses an ex-boyfriend of raping her, but when the search turns to her dysfunctional family, surprise discoveries are made. From an overly helpful father, mysterious children, an over-affectionate little girl, a bracelet and, finally, sperm from two men who never raped, SVU discovers that the family is even worse off than they thought

The detectives have very little to work with after a man is found badly-beaten in a strip club's parking lot. Their questioning begins with the dancers, until the victim's ex-wife and 13-year-old transgender son become suspects.
